  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A prospective randomized clinical trial. Cervical spondylotic foraminal stenosis with
      radiculopahty. Comparison results between 2 treatment options: ACDF and minimal invasive
      posterior cervical foraminiotomy.

      80 patients to be followed for 2 years. Parameters to study: NDI, VAS, EQ-5D, complications,
      health economics, recurrens of stenosis, movement of facet joints pre- and postoperatively
      (foraminotomy group).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
